<div id="code-to-describe-and-show-a-strategy-for-imputing-missing-data" class="section level1">
<h1>Code to describe and show a strategy for imputing missing data</h1>
<pre class="r"><code class="hljs">NATotal &lt;- sum(!complete.cases(data))
NATotal</code></pre>
<pre><code class="hljs">## [1] 2304</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code class="hljs">StepsAverage &lt;- aggregate(steps ~ interval, data = data, FUN = mean)
fillNA &lt;- numeric()
<span class="hljs-keyword">for</span> (i <span class="hljs-keyword">in</span> <span class="hljs-number">1</span>:nrow(data)) {
  obs &lt;- data[i, ]
  <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (is.na(obs$steps)) {
    steps &lt;- subset(StepsAverage, interval == obs$interval)$steps
  } <span class="hljs-keyword">else</span> {
    steps &lt;- obs$steps
  }
  fillNA &lt;- c(fillNA, steps)
}

new_activity &lt;- data
new_activity$steps &lt;- fillNA</code></pre>
</div>
